    "To compare with data, it is customary to quote helium-4 in terms of the primordial mass fractionfoot_7 Y P ≡ 4 × Y4 He ρ4 He /ρ B.",
    "(21)The other primordial elements under the lamppost of astrophysical observations are deuterium, helium-3 and lithium-7 (see, e.g., [11] for a recent report on the status of these measurements), which are usually quoted in terms of the relative number densities with respect to hydrogen: 3 He, 7 Li.i/H ≡ Y i /Y p = n i /n H, where i = D,()22Notice that the final yield of primordial helium-3 receives a contribution from unstable species such as tritium; likewise, the final amount of lithium-7 includes the decay of beryllium-7.The literature contains several publicly accessible compilations of the thermonuclear rates relevant for BBN."
